<item>
 <title>Keith Jarrett</title>
 <link>http://jazz.to/artist/keith-jarrett-0</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-photo field-type-image field-label-hidden field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://jazz.to/sites/default/files/keith-jarrett.jpg&quot; width=&quot;250&quot; height=&quot;233&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;body field&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Keith Jarrett, considered by many to be a genius, is among the most creative musi­cians working in contemporary jazz. He burst onto the scene in the early 60s, first with Charles Lloyd and then with Miles Davis. He went on to launch a prolific solo career marked by several phases and rich collaborations. Jarrett&#039;s improvisational solo concerts from the 1970s are widely viewed as classics. He has also made scores of straight-up jazz recordings with his trio as well as classical recordings. Keith Jarrett enjoys a virtual cult following all over the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-video field-type-file field-label-hidden field-wrapper&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;media-youtube-video media-youtube-1&quot;&gt;
